$NVDA Has anyone heard any details of semiconductor demand softening as referenced below? 
 
Nvidia price target lowered to $255 from $285 at Deutsche Bank 
 
Deutsche Bank analyst Ross Seymore lowered the firm's price target on Nvidia to $255 from $285 and keeps a Hold rating on the shares. The "purgatory" stage of the semiconductor cycle appears to be in full effect heading into the Q1 earnings reports, Seymore tells investors in a research note. Fundamentally, he expects revenue and earnings strength to persist with semiconductor demand exceeding supply. However, despite these positive fundamentals, Seymore believes recent investor concerns of a cyclical slowdown/correction are likely to persist as supply loosens and demand potentially softens.

$NVDA Nvidia will be active buying back shares, says Piper Sandler 
 
Piper Sandler analyst Harsh Kumar reiterates a Buy rating on Nvidia with a $350 price target ahead of the company's earnings report. The China COVID supply risk remains something worth monitoring but the risk from Russia demand is "quite manageable" given the supply constraints, Kumar tells investors in a research note. The analyst believes Nvidia remains on track to hit supply/demand equilibrium in the second half of 2022. In addition, management will be active with its current share repurchase authorization given the stock's retreat and the company's sizable cash position, Kumar contends. He the company's "steady cadence of new product launches helping to offset concerns about seasonality."
